Mark,

I suspect the problem is that the Cantera Python extension module was 
built to link to one version of the Python DLL, and can&#39;t be used with 
a different version.  Try running the temporary Python file that 
ct2ctml creates, and see what error message it gives you.  If this is 
the problem, you can build it from the source with whatever Python 
version you like.

Dave




